Kim Yong Nam meets government delegation of Benin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly,  met and conversed with the government delegation of Benin led by Antoine Idji Kolawole,  Minister of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation asked him to convey wholehearted greetings of President Mathieu Kerekou to the great leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Witnessing the astonishing achievements made by the DPRK itself even under the most difficult conditions, the delegation came to have conviction that the Beninese people are sure to build a nice country, if they do as the Korean people did, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He conveyed the full support of the Beninese government and people to the struggle of the Korean people.

Kim Yong Nam meets congratulatory group and delegations of Chongryon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, met and conversed with a congratulatory group and delegations of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), which participated in the celebrations of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Chongryon delegations including a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan to celebrate the 55th WPK anniversary headed by chief vice-chairman of the Chongryon central standing committee Ho Jong Man, a delegation of Korean businessmen in Japan, a delegation of Chongryon officials and  a contingent of relay racers of carrying letters of loyalty of 700,000 Koreans in Japan.

Vice-president of SPA presidium meets leading officials of IIJI 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, member of the political bureau of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, met and conversed with the party and state delegation of the Lao people's Democratic Republic led by Samane Vignaket, member of the political bureau of the central committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party and president of the National Assembly of Laos, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Pak Kil Yon, vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs, officials concerned and Khamkheng Sayakeo, Lao ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation said that the Lao party, state and people would fully support the Worker's Party of Korea and the DPRK government in the efforts to achieve the cause of the reunification of the country in hearty response to the behest of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed firm belief that the Korean people would surely build a powerful nation under the leadership of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam met and had a conversation with Ludger Volmer, Minister of State of the Ministry for Foreign Affairs of Germany, and his party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Choe Su Hon, vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs of the DPRK, and Thomas Wulfing, representative of the interest section for the Federal Republic of Germany here.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from chairman of c.c., Lao People's Revolutionary Party 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a gift from Khamtay Siphandone, chairman of the central committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party and President of the Lao People's Democratic Republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It was handed to Yang Hyong Sop, alternate member of the political bureau of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and vice-president of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, by Samane Vignaket, member of the political bureau of the central committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party and president of the National Assembly of Laos who is on a visit to Korea.

Reception given for delegations and personages of organizations for study of Juche idea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- The Korean Social Scientists Society hosted a reception at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on Oct. 15 in honor of the visiting delegations and personages of organizations for the study of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and chairman of the society, in his address made at the reception said that thanks to energetic activities and efforts of the organizations and personages new organizations for the study of the Juche idea were inaugurated in many countries of the world and their activities have rapidly gained in scope among broad masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that the organizations and personages studying the Juche idea would steadily expand the ranks of Juche idea followers in various forms and methods in the future, too.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Director general Vishwanath of the International Institute of the Juche Idea in his address said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The enormous successes made by the Korean people in recent years under the leadership of the Worker's Party of Korea greatly encourage the Juche idea followers. They are deeply impressed by the great army-first politics, the unique political mode of the great leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is a great thinker, statesman and beacon who illumines the way to be followed by the times with brilliant rays, holding aloft the banner of socialism, he said, adding: We firmly believe that the Korean people will surely build a reunified powerful nation under his leadership.

Monument to Kim Il Sung's impromptu poem erected 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- A monument to the great leader President Kim Il Sung's famous poem "On Autumnal Day on Mt. Myohyang" was erected in the yard of the international friendship exhibition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President visited the exhibition on Mt. Myohyang, a famous mountain of Korea, on Oct. 15, Juche 68(1979). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At that time, he recited an impromptu poem on a veranda of the fifth floor of the exhibition, commanding a bird's eye-view of picturesque Mt. Myohyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The poem carries the President's noble intention to bolster up the people's honor and pride that the Korean nation is the best and convey the new history of the era of the worker's party through generations to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The poem is carved on a huge granite monument. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony of unveiling the monument took place there on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony was secretary Kim Jung Rin of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea.

Kim Jong Il arranges reception for congratulatory group and delegations of Chongryon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- The great leader Kim Jong Il arranged a reception at the Mokran House on Sunday in honor of the congratulatory group and delegations of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan that participated in the celebrations of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the reception was President Kim Yong Nam of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there were the congratulatory group of Korean residents in Japan to celebrate the 55th birthday of the WPK, the delegation of Korean traders and industrialists in Japan, the delegation of Chongryon officials, the contingent of relay racers to convey letters of loyalty of the 700,000  Korean residents in Japan and members of various Chongryon delegations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Sun, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, said in his speech that the significant reception is associated with the particular trust and tender-hearted fatherly love shown by the respected Kim Jong Il for Chongryon and the Korean residents in Japan, who have invariably advanced  along the patriotic road despite difficult conditions in an alien land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has conducted indefatigable activities to provide leadership day and night, shouldering upon himself all the heavy burdens  of steering the cause of building a powerful socialist nation, the cause of Korea's reunification and the cause of global independence, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the forthcoming 21st century will shine as a glorious Kim Jong Il century when a reunified powerful nation will tower high to lead the world, he stressed all the officials of Chongryon should make a tangible contribution to building a powerful nation in the homeland and achieving Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Head of the congratulatory group Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the central standing committee of Chongryon, extended deepest thanks to Kim Jong Il for inviting them to visit the socialist homeland and arranging a grand reception and repeatedly granting lavish best privilege and preferential treatment to them, representing the unanimous wishes of all the officials of Chongryon and 700,000 Korean residents in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that they once again deeply cherished the fixed faith and optimism while participating in the world startling October celebrations that a reunified powerful nation is sure to be built under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, he said that they would conduct better the patriotic work as intended by him.

Party Founding Museum 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- An endless stream of people from all walks of life visited the Party Founding Museum on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea (October 10, 1945). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The museum situated in the center of Pyongyang was opened in October Juche 59 (1970). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Office rooms, a drawing room and a conference hall are preserved in their original state. There the President Kim Il Sung worked right after the liberation of the country on August 15, Juche 34 (1945). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display there are hundreds of materials and relics showing the revolutionary exploits the President performed by founding the party and achieving the cause of building the country and the army after his triumphant  return home. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The office rooms used by the President are on the first floor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There he worked out and published the program and the draft rules of the party and authored many famous works including the report to the inaugural party congress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are precious relics showing these historical facts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was in the conference hall on the first floor that the President called the historic inaugural party congress and proclaimed the foundation of the party to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are seven rooms on the ground floor where historic materials are exhibited. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A hundred meters away from the building there is the lodging quarters where the President shared board and room with his revolutionary comrades in those days when he worked to found the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There he dispatched anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters to all parts of the country to make preparations for the party founding and met and gave precious instructions to figures from all walks of life from different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The monument to the party foundation "never-to-be-forgotten historic house" is standing near the museum.

Korean books presented to Guyana 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of presenting  Korean books was held at the building of the linden city office on Oct.6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony the Korean ambassador to Guyana conveyed famous works of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il including the reminiscences "With the Century" and other Korean books to Mayor of Linden Stanley Smith and chairman of the City Council Henri Hamilton. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mayor said in his speech that those books would serve as most precious textbooks to deeply study the Juche idea which was founded by Kim Il Sung and enriched by Kim Jong Il.

Rodong Sinmun calls on all to turn out in building powerful nation 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today editorially calls upon the party members, servicepersons and people to more vigorously accelerate the historic advance for the building of a powerful nation with the same vim and vigor as were displayed in glorifying the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea as a grand festival of victors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK's 55th anniversary was a grand festival of socialist victors who powerfully demonstrated the indomitable spirit and the might of the single-hearted unity of the Korean people which have grown stronger than ever before under the army-first revolutionary leadership of the respected Kim Jong Il, the editorial says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the celebrations the Korean People's Army and people renewed their firm pledge to glorify the WPK as a party of the great Kim Il Sung, always holding him in high esteem as the eternal leader of the party and the revolution. They also cherished more deeply the immovable faith that the way indicated by Kim Jong Il and led by the WPK is the most just one and the cause of building a powerful socialist nation is sure to win. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to speed up the historic advance for the building of a powerful nation, all the party members, servicepersons and people should, first of all, remain unfailingly loyal to his army-first revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should glorify forever the immortal exploits he has performed in his army-first revolutionary leadership by leading the historic "arduous march" and the forced march and ushering in a new era of prosperity and development as the eternal assets of the party and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial underscores the need to implement the line of attaching great importance to the ideology, army and science and technology and thus increase in every way the politico- ideological might of the revolutionary ranks and the combat capability of the people's army and develop the economy into a viable and totally independent one based on advanced science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It further says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary spirit of soldiers and the Kanggye spirit created by Kim Jong Il represent the spirit in the present era of building a powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Let's always be cheerful although our path is thorny " this is a slogan of struggle and optimism for our army and people who glorified the honor of being socialist victors under his leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should build better the streets and villages, factories and workplaces to be suited to socialism, a powerful nation, loudly singing the song of revolution, the song of struggle.

Kim Jong Il receives floral basket and congratulatory visiting card 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 16 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a floral basket and a congratulatory visiting card from Abou Bacar Sompare, general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea, on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary paid a congratulatory visit to the Korean embassy in Conakry on October 10 and conveyed them to the ambassador. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the card are words: "I most sincerely wish he Kim Jong Il a long life in good health. Abou Bacar Sompare, general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea".
